{
  "page": "Old Man of the River",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">This article is about the Rhoynish deity. For the species of giant turtles, see <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Men_of_the_River\" title=\"Old Men of the River\">Old Men of the River</a>. For the Braavosi ship insurer, see <a href=\"/index.php/Old_man\" title=\"Old man\">old man</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9c/Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg/350px-Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"313\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9c/Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg/525px-Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9c/Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg/700px-Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Old_Man_of_the_River.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Yandry\" title=\"Yandry\">Yandry</a> claims this huge horned turtle is the Old Man of the River. Art by Puppy-Chow ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Old Man of the River</b> is a lesser god of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoynar\" title=\"Rhoynar\">Rhoynar</a>. He is the son of <a href=\"/index.php/Mother_Rhoyne\" title=\"Mother Rhoyne\">Mother Rhoyne</a>, and his form is that of a giant <a href=\"/index.php/Turtle\" title=\"Turtle\">turtle</a>. According to Rhoynar beliefs, the Old Man of the River fought the <a href=\"/index.php/Crab_King\" title=\"Crab King\">Crab King</a> for dominion of all life below the flowing water.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The giant turtles of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoyne\" title=\"Rhoyne\">Rhoyne</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Men_of_the_River\" title=\"Old Men of the River\">Old Men of the River</a>, are named after him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf28.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf28.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_Man_of_the_River&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_Man_of_the_River&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Garin_(orphan)\" title=\"Garin (orphan)\">Garin</a> explains the history of the <a href=\"/index.php/Orphans_of_the_Greenblood\" title=\"Orphans of the Greenblood\">orphans of the Greenblood</a> to Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Myrcella_Baratheon\" title=\"Myrcella Baratheon\">Myrcella Baratheon</a>, including their devotion to <a href=\"/index.php/Mother_Rhoyne\" title=\"Mother Rhoyne\">Mother Rhoyne</a>. When Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arys_Oakheart\" title=\"Arys Oakheart\">Arys Oakheart</a> says that he had heard the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoynar\" title=\"Rhoynar\">Rhoynar</a> worshipped a turtle god, Garin explains that the Old Man of the River is a lesser god, the child of Mother Rhoyne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_Man_of_the_River&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Shy_Maid\" title=\"Shy Maid\">Shy Maid</a></i> sails down the Rhoyne at <a href=\"/index.php/Ny_Sar\" title=\"Ny Sar\">Ny Sar</a>, they see a <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Men_of_the_River\" title=\"Old Men of the River\">huge horned turtle</a>, which <a href=\"/index.php/Yandry\" title=\"Yandry\">Yandry</a> claims is the Old Man of the River himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_Man_of_the_River&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_21\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 21\">Chapter 21</a>, The Queenmaker.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf28.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf28.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Ancient History&#58; Ten Thousand Ships.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Tyrion IV.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowrapli